quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  43,16,"Or has He taken to Himself, from that He creates, daughters, and favoured you with sons"
  43,17,"And when any of them is given the good tidings of that he has likened to the All-merciful, his face is darkened, and he chokes inwardly"
  43,18,"What, one who is reared amid ornaments and, when the time of altercation comes, is not to be seen"
  43,19,"And they have made the angels, who are themselves servants of the All-merciful, females. What, did they witness their creation? Their witness shall be written down, and they shall be questioned"
  43,20,"They say, 'Had the All-merciful so willed, we would not have served them.' They have no knowledge of that; they are only conjecturing"
  43,21,Or did We bring them a Book aforetime to which they hold
  43,22,"Nay, but they say, 'We found our fathers upon a community, and we are guided upon their traces"
  43,23,"Even so We sent never before thee any warner into any city, except that its men who lived at ease said, 'We indeed found our fathers upon a community, and we are following upon their traces"
  43,24,"Say: 'What, though I should bring you a better guidance than you found your fathers upon?' They say, 'We disbelieve in that you were sent with"
  43,25,So We took vengeance upon them; and behold how was the end of them that cried lies